Here is the JavaScript construct to calculate the factorial of a non-negative integer variable `x`, initialized to 7:

```javascript
// Assign the variable x a concrete value of 7
let x = 7;

// Function to calculate factorial
function calculateFactorial(n) {
    if (n < 0) {
        throw new Error("Input must be a non-negative integer.");
    }
    if (n === 0 || n === 1) {
        return 1;
    }
    let result = 1;
    for (let i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
        result *= i;
    }
    return result;
}

// Calculate and display the result
const factorialOfX = calculateFactorial(x);
console.log(`The factorial of ${x} is: ${factorialOfX}`);
```

This code ensures that `x` is treated as a non-negative integer and computes the product of all positive integers up to `x`.
